# UI design rules

## Fintech aesthetic

- Calm, trustworthy, minimal — not flashy or gamified
- Generous whitespace; avoid cramming data
- Muted color palette with one accent color for primary actions
- Numbers are the hero — typography should make amounts scannable
- No gradients, glow effects, or heavy shadows unless explicitly requested

## Typography

- Page titles: `text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight`
- Section headings: `text-lg font-medium`
- Body: `text-sm` (default shadcn scale)
- Monetary amounts: `font-mono tabular-nums` for alignment in tables
- Secondary/meta text: `text-muted-foreground text-xs`
- Negative amounts (expenses): subtle red in light mode, muted red in dark mode
- Positive amounts (income): subtle green — use sparingly, not for every positive number

## Card layouts

- Summary KPI cards: label on top, large number below, optional trend indicator
- Use shadcn `Card` with consistent padding (`p-6`)
- Grid: `grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4` for dashboard KPIs
- No nested cards — flatten hierarchy with spacing instead

## Table spacing

- Row height: comfortable (`py-3` minimum)
- Column padding: `px-4`
- Right-align numeric columns; left-align text columns
- Zebra striping optional — prefer subtle row hover instead
- Action buttons in the last column, right-aligned, icon-only with tooltips

## Dashboard hierarchy

1. Page title + date range + primary action (top bar)
2. KPI summary cards (net worth, cash flow, spending, income)
3. Charts (spending by category, trend over time)
4. Detail tables (recent transactions, upcoming recurring)

Each level separated by `space-y-6` or `gap-6`.

## Color usage

- Primary action: accent color (one per theme)
- Destructive: red for delete/remove only
- Status indicators: muted badges — `default`, `secondary`, `outline` variants
- Charts: max 6–8 distinct colors; use a fixed palette for category consistency
- Do not use color alone to convey meaning — always pair with label or icon

## Dark mode

- All new components must work in both light and dark mode
- Use CSS variables from shadcn theme (`bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `border-border`)
- Test contrast in both modes before shipping
- Charts: use theme-aware colors, not hardcoded hex values
- Avoid pure black backgrounds — use `bg-background` token

## Icons and density

- Use lucide-react icons consistently
- Icon size: `h-4 w-4` inline, `h-5 w-5` in buttons
- Power-user density: support a compact table view option in the future — default to comfortable spacing now

## Motion

- Minimal animation — subtle transitions on hover/focus only
- No animated number counters or confetti
- Page transitions: none (App Router default)
